# utils
def download_data(
    ticker: str,
    year: int,
    month: int = None,
) -> str:
    """Download 1min OHLC data from histdata.com to `./data`
    """
    if datetime.datetime.now().year != year:
        month = None
    path = dl(year=str(year), month=month, pair=ticker, platform=P.META_TRADER, time_frame=TF.ONE_MINUTE, output_directory="data/zip")
    shutil.unpack_archive(path, extract_dir="data/")
    return path

def load_data(
    ticker: str = "USDJPY",
    year: Union[int, List[int]] = 2015,
    month: int = None,
) -> pd.DataFrame:
    """Load 1min-OHLC data. (Download from histdata if not exists.)
    """
    if isinstance(year, Iterable):
        return pd.concat([load_data(ticker=ticker, year=_year, month=month) for _year in year])
    
    path = f"data/DAT_MT_{ticker.upper()}_M1_{year}.csv" if month is None else f"data/DAT_MT_{ticker.upper()}_M1_{year}{month:02d}.csv"
    if not Path(path).exists():
        download_data(ticker=ticker, year=year, month=month)
        
    data = pd.read_csv(path, names=["date", "time", "open", "high", "low", "close", "_"])
    data["timestamp"] = pd.to_datetime(data.date + " " + data.time).dt.tz_localize("EST").dt.tz_convert("UTC")
    data["ticker"] = ticker.upper()
    data["date"] = pd.to_datetime(data["date"])
    return data[["timestamp", "ticker", "open", "high", "low", "close"]]

# preprocessing
def to_ny17_date(time_index: pd.DatetimeIndex) -> np.ndarray:
    # return date with Daystart=NY17:00
    return pd.to_datetime(time_index.tz_convert("US/Eastern").shift(freq="7h").date)

def is_around_eoy(time_index: pd.DatetimeIndex) -> np.ndarray:
    # return True from Christmas to 3rd Jan.
    dates = to_ny17_date(time_index)
    return ((dates.month==1) & (dates.day<=3)) | ((dates.month==12) & (25<=dates.day))

# post processing
def to_confidence_quantile(prediction: pd.Series) -> pd.Series:
    # [!] just return quantile level for simplicity. qunatization should be done only with in-sample. 
    conf = pd.qcut(prediction.abs(), q=np.arange(0, 1.01, 0.01).round(4), labels=False, duplicates="drop")
    conf = (conf / conf.max()) * 100
    return conf

def calculate_macd(df: pd.DataFrame, short_window=12, long_window=26, signal_window=9):
    df['shortEMA'] = df['close'].ewm(span=short_window, min_periods=1, adjust=False).mean()
    df['longEMA'] = df['close'].ewm(span=long_window, min_periods=1, adjust=False).mean()
    df['macd'] = df['shortEMA'] - df['longEMA']
    df['signal'] = df['macd'].ewm(span=signal_window, min_periods=1, adjust=False).mean()
    return df.signal.rename("macd")

def calculate_rsi(df: pd.DataFrame, window=14) -> pd.Series:
    delta = df['close'].diff(1)
    gain = delta.where(delta > 0, 0)
    loss = -delta.where(delta < 0, 0)
    avg_gain = gain.rolling(window=window, min_periods=1).mean()
    avg_loss = loss.rolling(window=window, min_periods=1).mean()
    rs = avg_gain / avg_loss
    df['rsi'] = 100 - (100 / (1 + rs))
    return df.rsi

# metrics
def calc_annu_sharpe(pls: pd.Series) -> float:
    assert isinstance(pls.index, pd.DatetimeIndex)
    dates = to_ny17_date(pls.index)
    daily_pls = pls.groupby(dates).resample("1d").sum()
    return daily_pls.mean() / daily_pls.std() * np.sqrt(252)
    
def calc_max_draw_down(pls: pd.Series) -> float:
    assert isinstance(pls.index, pd.DatetimeIndex)
    return (pls.cumsum().cummax() - pls.cumsum()).max()

def calc_hit_ratio(pls: pd.Series) -> float:
    return (pls > 0).sum() / pls.shape[0]

def calc_performance_summary(
    signals: pd.DataFrame, 
    pl_name="pl",
    signal_name="pred",
    confidence_threshold=[0, 90]
) -> pd.DataFrame:
    if isinstance(confidence_threshold, Iterable):
        results = pd.concat([
            calc_performance_summary(signals, pl_name=pl_name, signal_name=signal_name, confidence_threshold=theta).set_axis([100-theta])
            for theta in confidence_threshold
        ])
        results.index.name = "coverage"
        return results
    else:
        _subset = signals.loc[confidence_threshold <= to_confidence_quantile(signals[signal_name])] if signal_name is not None else signals 
        return _subset[pl_name].describe().drop(["std", "75%", "25%"]).rename({"50%": "med"}).rename(lambda x: f"pl_{x}").to_frame("").T.assign(
            pl_total = _subset[pl_name].sum(),
            hit_ratio = calc_hit_ratio(_subset[pl_name]),
            sharpe = calc_annu_sharpe(_subset[pl_name]),
            max_dd = calc_max_draw_down(_subset[pl_name]),
        ).round(3)

Random signal¶

  • 500 sets of random daily Up/Down signals
  • calculate performance metrics for each signals.
In [22]:
daily_ret = daily_price.pct_change().mul(1e4).rename("daily_ret").dropna().loc[TEST_ST : TEST_ET]
def generate_random_prediction_dataset(seed=1):
    np.random.seed(seed)
    eval_data = daily_ret.to_frame("ret")
    eval_data["pred"] = np.random.choice([-1, 1], size=daily_ret.shape[0])
    eval_data["pl"] = eval_data.prod(axis=1)
    return eval_data

Simple linear¶

  • 1h sampling frequency.
  • $R_t := (Price(t) - Price(t-1)) / Price(t-1)$
  • features $X_t$:
    • $R_t$
    • $R_{t-1}$
    • $R_{t-2}$
  • target $y_t$:
    • $R_{t+1}$
  • model:
    • $R_{t+1} = \sum_{k=0}^{2} c_k R_{t-k}$
  1. Preprocessing
In [25]:
# Build 1hour freq `timestamp`-measurable OHLC
ohlc_1h = ohlc.set_index("timestamp").resample("1h").agg({"open": "first", "high": "max", "low": "min", "close": "last"}).shift(freq="1h")  # `timestamp`-measureble OHLC
ohlc_1h = ohlc_1h.loc[to_ny17_date(ohlc_1h.index).weekday < 5]
ohlc_1h = ohlc_1h.loc[~is_around_eoy(ohlc_1h.index)]
ohlc_1h["close"] = ohlc_1h.close.fillna(method="ffill")  # filled by latest valid close
ohlc_1h = ohlc_1h.fillna(method="bfill", axis=1)  # filled by close

# Price path around Tokyo fixing
price = ohlc.set_index("timestamp").open.between_time(datetime.time(0, 5), datetime.time(1, 50)).to_frame("price")
price["date"] = price.index.date
price["time"] = price.index.time.astype(str)
price = price.drop_duplicates()
prices = price.set_index(["date", "time"]).price.unstack(level=-1)
prices = (prices / prices.iloc[:, 0].values.reshape(-1, 1)).sub(1).mul(1e4)

# Calculate historical return 
price_toward_fix = ohlc.set_index("timestamp").open.between_time(datetime.time(0, 0), datetime.time(0, 50))
price_from_fix = ohlc.set_index("timestamp").open.between_time(datetime.time(0, 50), datetime.time(1, 20))
ret_toward_fix = price_toward_fix.groupby(price_toward_fix.index.date).agg(["first", "last"]).pct_change(axis=1).mul(1e4).iloc[:, -1].rename("ret")
ret_from_fix = price_from_fix.groupby(price_from_fix.index.date).agg(["first", "last"]).pct_change(axis=1).mul(-1e4).iloc[:, -1].rename("ret")
tkyfix = ret_toward_fix.to_frame("pl").assign(pred=+1).append(ret_from_fix.to_frame("pl").assign(pred=-1))
tkyfix.index = pd.to_datetime(tkyfix.index).tz_localize("UTC")
tkyfix["after_2019"] = tkyfix.index.year >= 2019
tkyfix = tkyfix.sort_index()

calc_performance_summary2 = partial(calc_performance_summary, signal_name=None, confidence_threshold=None)

++Gotoubi flag¶

Dates divisible by 5 are known as "Gotoubi"().
On these dates, stronger demand for dollars from Japanese companies is likely to promote dollar buying and yen selling.

In [43]:
# generate gotoubi dates
dates = pd.date_range("2000-01-01", "2040-01-01")
jpn_holidays = pd.to_datetime(list(holidays.Japan(years=range(2000, 2040)).keys()))
gotoubi = dates[(dates.day%5) == 0]
gotoubi = pd.Index([date - pd.offsets.BDay(int(date.weekday()>4)) for date in gotoubi])
gotoubi = pd.Index([date - pd.offsets.BDay(int(date in jpn_holidays)) for date in gotoubi])
In [44]:
tkyfix["is_gotoubi"] = to_ny17_date(tkyfix.index).isin(gotoubi)
tkyfix["selected"] = (tkyfix.is_gotoubi & (tkyfix.pred > 0)) | ((~tkyfix.is_gotoubi) & (tkyfix.pred < 0))
